<p>Russia said it will run return-only flights from Cuba, effectively bringing Russian tourists home as a fuel shortage disrupts aviation and daily life on the island. Travel coverage warned the situation could sharply curtail — or even halt — parts of Cuba’s tourism industry, leaving many visitors with a very different trip than planned. The reports tie the crunch to tougher US measures under President Trump that raise pressure on Cuba and affect oil supply and shipments, a step some outlets describe as a “fuel blockade”. Cuba has said it is reserving what fuel it has for essential services as transport and power come under strain.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/UPdplcYxebJZ-ibVIcTDlhVXZLJWhrB09Ete6TKfZ-9LH4RGEWJJUhFAfqZZzT9brCuvA_f8jskw4ryJWXGuZqyzJ6D_kh-Ayj21n-Ken_3Rv6uoUTfK3ET6VGNMq2RI-cnJJ4RnNiregq_v52caTkBnVgfRj7VZOuQGE8zPwZHgsydz5tCjHtkHKFjGDKRYgBfjcmYQ7oGJjE_uFKOEi82T8QhDU0ikT2Dh5cS3TnUI3p2-UrLFl_ggdXZG' alt='Airport and transport disruptions as Cuba faces fuel shortages.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tourists affected: Russia’s Association of Tour Operators said about 5,000 Russian tourists were in Cuba as return-focused flights from Havana and Varadero to Moscow were arranged.</li><li>Power and transport disruption: Coverage described rolling blackouts, reduced transport, and grounded flights as fuel scarcity deepens.</li><li>Workweek changes: Cuban state companies were reported to be preparing a shift to a four-day workweek as authorities ration fuel and scale back interprovincial transport.</li><li>Regional balancing: The Christian Science Monitor described Mexico as trying to balance its 124-year relationship with Cuba against a US crackdown targeting international oil shipments to the island.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Russian authorities and tour operators: Russia planned return-only flights from Cuba to get tourists home, describing the worsening fuel shortages as a US-engineered crisis. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/12/russia-to-evacuate-tourists-from-cuba-amid-us-engineered-fuel-crisis'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>China’s foreign ministry: A spokesperson said China would “do what it can” to support Cuba and condemned the US measures, according to the report. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3343242/china-vows-do-what-it-can-us-blockade-leaves-cuba-just-weeks-oil'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Cuban government: Officials said they would prioritise available fuel for essential services and indispensable economic activities, according to the report. (<a href='https://theweek.com/world-news/cuba-fuel-crisis-trump-blockade'>The Week</a>)</li><li>United Nations: A UN spokesperson warned the humanitarian situation could worsen if Cuba’s oil needs are not met, according to the report. (<a href='https://theweek.com/world-news/cuba-fuel-crisis-trump-blockade'>The Week</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/12/russia-to-evacuate-tourists-from-cuba-amid-us-engineered-fuel-crisis'>Russia evacuates tourists from Cuba as US-engineered fuel crisis deepens</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3343242/china-vows-do-what-it-can-us-blockade-leaves-cuba-just-weeks-oil'>China vows to ‘do what it can’ as US blockade leaves Cuba with just weeks of oil</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Americas/2026/0211/cuba-air-canada-fuel-mexico'>As U.S. stymies oil imports to Cuba, Mexico plays a balancing act</a> - csmonitor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1r2ckqb/moscow_preparing_to_evacuate_russian_tourists/'>Moscow preparing to evacuate Russian tourists from Cuba amid US oil blockade</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/lifestyle/cubas-tourism-might-face-a-complete-shutdown-heres-what-travellers-should-know-13978619.html'>Cuba&#x27;s tourism might face a complete shutdown. Here&#x27;s wha